@startuml
title DAR Submission Queue - Sequence Diagram (Physical Server Deployment)

actor SupervisorA as A
actor SupervisorB as B
participant "main_dar_app\n(Flutter)" as AppA
participant "main_dar_app\n(Flutter)" as AppB
participant "DAR_Middleware\n(Node/Express on Physical Server)" as API
database "MSSQL DAR DB" as DB
participant "Reaper Timer\n(setInterval)" as Reaper

== User taps Send to Server ==
A -> AppA: Tap Send
AppA -> API: POST /queue/enqueue {supervisorId,userId,reportCount}
API -> DB: Check existing WAITING/ACTIVE for supervisor
alt No existing session
  API -> DB: Insert WAITING session (SessionId=101)
  API -> AppA: {sessionId:101, position:1}
else Existing session
  API -> AppA: Return existing sessionId + position
end

B -> AppB: Tap Send
AppB -> API: POST /queue/enqueue {supervisorId,userId,reportCount}
API -> DB: Check existing WAITING/ACTIVE
API -> DB: Insert WAITING session (SessionId=102)
API -> AppB: {sessionId:102, position:2}

== Polling for turn ==
loop Every 3 seconds
  AppA -> API: POST /queue/check-turn {sessionId:101}
  API -> DB: Expire stale ACTIVE sessions (if any)
  API -> DB: Transaction + UPDLOCK/HOLDLOCK\nactivate oldest WAITING if no ACTIVE
  API -> AppA: {isMyTurn:true, position:1, status:ACTIVE}
end

loop Every 3 seconds
  AppB -> API: POST /queue/check-turn {sessionId:102}
  API -> DB: Expire stale ACTIVE sessions (if any)
  API -> DB: Detect ACTIVE=101\nkeep 102 as WAITING
  API -> AppB: {isMyTurn:false, position:2, status:WAITING}
end

== Active user runs existing DAR pipeline ==
AppA -> API: POST /sendDARForm/... batch
API -> DB: Write tblDARbatch
AppA -> API: POST /sendDARForm/... hdr
API -> DB: Write tblDARhdr + tbldocno updates
AppA -> API: POST /sendDARForm/... dtls/accomp/materials
API -> DB: Write DAR detail tables
AppA -> API: PUT /sendDARForm/utilities/calculateTotalsHdr
API -> DB: Update totals
AppA -> API: PUT /sendDARForm/utilities/calculateTotalsBatch
API -> DB: Update totals

alt Pipeline success
  AppA -> API: POST /queue/complete {sessionId:101}
  API -> DB: Update status=COMPLETED, completedAt=now
  API -> AppA: 200 OK
else Pipeline failure
  AppA -> API: POST /queue/fail {sessionId:101, reason}
  API -> DB: Update status=FAILED, completedAt=now
  API -> AppA: 200 OK
end

== Next user proceeds ==
AppB -> API: POST /queue/check-turn {sessionId:102}
API -> DB: Activate next WAITING (102 -> ACTIVE)
API -> AppB: {isMyTurn:true, position:1, status:ACTIVE}
AppB -> API: (Run same /sendDARForm pipeline)
AppB -> API: POST /queue/complete {sessionId:102}

== Background stale-session protection ==
loop Every QUEUE_REAPER_INTERVAL_MS
  Reaper -> API: Trigger expireStale()
  API -> DB: ACTIVE older than TTL -> EXPIRED
end

@enduml
